@238 = ~Faldorn, the way you talk about nature and man - both can coexist peacefully.~
@239 = ~I will not listen to the ramblings of a betrayer.~
@240 = ~I didn't betray anyone.~
@241 = ~You have betrayed the woods, the river, the inhabitants... the true innocent.~
@242 = ~No, I fight for the goodness in all life. Everyone and everything deserve to live.~
@243 = ~And this is where we differ, you and me. I am realistic and you are not.~
@244 = ~There is no point in speaking to someone so far gone.~